{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0357922b-9353-4db6-b2c0-b79d05ef5d27","content":"The working directory is empty, so I'll provide guidance based on the skill-validator evaluation format referenced in this environment.\n\n## Evaluation Format (`evaluation.yml`)\n\nEvaluations use a YAML file with questions that test whether an LLM can correctly invoke your MCP tools:\n\n```yaml\nquestions:\n  - text: \"What is the price of the 'Ultra Widget Pro'?\"\n    expectedToolCalls:\n      - toolName: \"get_product\"\n        arguments:\n          name: \"Ultra Widget Pro\"\n    expectedResponseContains:\n      - \"$49.99\"\n\n  - text: \"Show me all products in the 'Electronics' category under $100\"\n    expectedToolCalls:\n      - toolName: \"search_products\"\n        arguments:\n          category: \"Electronics\"\n          maxPrice: 100\n```\n\n## What Makes a Good Evaluation Question\n\n| Quality | Example |\n|---------|---------|\n| **Specific & verifiable** | \"What's the SKU for Widget X?\" (one right answer) |\n| **Requires correct tool selection** | A question where multiple tools exist but only one is appropriate |\n| **Tests argument extraction** | \"Find red shoes in size 10\" → tests multiple params |\n| **Tests multi-step reasoning** | \"Which category has the most expensive average price?\" → requires multiple calls |\n| **Tests edge cases** | Misspellings, ambiguous names, empty results |\n\n## Tips\n\n1. **Cover each tool** — at least 2–3 questions per tool\n2. **Vary complexity** — mix single-call and multi-call scenarios\n3. **Include negative cases** — queries that should return \"not found\"\n4. **Use `expectedResponseContains`** for factual answers and `expectedToolCalls` for verifying correct invocation\n5. **Avoid ambiguity** — each question should have one clearly correct tool-calling strategy\n\nWould you like me to scaffold an `evaluation.yml` for your specific catalog tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"185f048f-2cb5-4fbc-b030-93fc603ede5e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty. Let me check if there's a skill-validator tool mentioned in the custom instructions that has documentation about evaluations. The custom instructions mention `eng/skill-validator/src/docs/InvestigatingResults.md` and an `evaluation.yml` file. Let me search more broadly or just provide guidance based on the custom instructions context.\n\nSince the directory is empty and there's no repo to reference, I'll provide guidance based on general knowledge of MCP skill evaluations and the skill-validator format mentioned in the custom instructions (which references `evaluation.yml` format).","outputTokens":595,"requestId":"2C14:2D9A4B:2A29A96:2E7DC72:69FD358E"},"id":"7f9e5fa4-cba3-4398-b6d8-b4c19270d970","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:00:13.974Z","parentId":"c703c872-a280-4b29-9a3c-ab893c46bee0"}
